# McpKit — Absorption Justification

**Date:** 2026-06-23
**Repository:** `KooshaPari/McpKit`
**Owner:** kooshapari
**Source Evidence:** `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/` (README, BRANCH_PROVENANCE, sessions, sladge-badge-scripts)
**Local Path:** not present on disk (no clone at `C:\Users\koosh\McpKit`); canonical evidence is the branch-only archive
**Default Branch:** `main` (archived at `c557c3c`, 2026-06-17)
**Remote State:** read-only archive since 2026-06-17; 90-day retention expires 2026-09-15 if not extended
**Verdict:** **HARD_DELETE_READY**
**Confidence:** HIGH
**Rubric Target:** P1 = 3, P2 = 3, P3 = 2, P4 = 2, P5 = 1
**Audit Cycle:** 2026-06-23 (phenotype-org-audits consolidation sweep)
**ADRs Invoked:** ADR-003 (McpKit → PhenoMCP merge), ADR-029 (Dmouse92 → KooshaPari canonical-owner migration)

---

## Source

The source repository `KooshaPari/McpKit` is the canonical-owner result of the 2026-06-17 Dmouse92 → KooshaPari migration, archived on the same day per ADR-029. The canonical remote is read-only with `archived: true`. Per ADR-003 (2026-06-14), McpKit content is merged into `PhenoMCP`; the McpKit branch-only archive at `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/` preserves 29 unique files (~316 KB total) that lived only on non-`main` branches and would otherwise be lost when local refs expire. The archive contains: `MCP_TOOLKITS_SOTA.md` (3,638 lines from `origin/feat/journey-impl@6b6156a`), `journey-traceability-RICH.md` (79 lines from commit `430a882`), two session directories (`sessions/20260428-taskfile-mcpkit/` and `sessions/20260429-mcpkit-sladge-badge/` — 14 files total from `origin/feat/journey-impl@6b6156a`), and the sladge-badge-scripts (`cmd/generate/*.go` + README + LICENSE + demo.cast — 11 files from local `docs/mcpkit-sladge-badge@971a6c7`). The branch provenance table records 9 source refs: 4 remote (`origin/main`, `origin/feat/journey-impl`, `origin/chore/1st-hygiene-2026-06-08`, `origin/wip/2026-06-18-McpKit-l7-001-propagation`) and 5 local-only (`docs/mcpkit-sladge-badge`, `docs/mcpkit-sladge-ci-refresh`, `chore/audit-safe-workflows-0605`, `chore/audit-safe-workflows-0605-r2`, `fix/trufflehog-setup-pin-0605`). The local-only branches never received a remote push before the archive, so they exist only in worktree refs. The branch-only archive is the recovery mechanism for these local-only refs.

