The four absorption targets (substrate, phenotype-python-sdk, phenotype-mcp-asset, Agentora) collectively cover the McpKit surface. The parity delta is essentially zero because the content has been absorbed and the targets have published the absorbed surface. The branch-only archive preserves the aspirational/SOTA research content (`MCP_TOOLKITS_SOTA.md`, journey-traceability rich version) which never made it into production code — that content is preserved as historical material, not absorbed as active code.

