| Rich journey-traceability | preserved in archive | not absorbed (research material) | none (out of scope) |

## Gaps and Exceptions

There are no capability gaps to record: all active content has been absorbed; all branch-only content has been preserved in the archive; the canonical remote is archived and ready for deletion after the retention window. There are no last-resort exceptions invoked in this cycle. The "with research material" disposition is itself the audit-cycle mechanism for acknowledging that aspirational/SOTA content is preserved-but-not-absorbed — it is not a gap and it is not an exception, it is a documented disposition.

| Gap | Severity | Owner | Resolution |
|---|---|---|---|
| 90-day retention gate | timing | audit | wait until 2026-09-15, then `gh repo delete` |
| Branch-only archive completeness | informational | audit | all 29 files captured per BRANCH_PROVENANCE |
| Aspirational SOTA content | informational | archive | preserved-as-research-material |
| Local-only branches never pushed | structural | audit | preserved in archive |

## Last-Resort-Exceptions

This audit cycle invokes **no last-resort exceptions**. The verdict `HARD_DELETE_READY` does not require a carve-out because:

1. **Rebuttal:** "We should not delete because branch-only content might be needed." **Rebutted:** the branch-only content has already been preserved in `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/` per its BRANCH_PROVENANCE — 29 files, ~316 KB, full commit-hash and byte-size provenance. Deletion of the canonical remote does not destroy this preserved material.
2. **Rebuttal:** "We should re-classify as `ARCHIVE_ONLY` since the remote is already archived." **Rebutted:** `ARCHIVE_ONLY` is appropriate when there is no absorption target; here there are four absorption targets (substrate, phenotype-python-sdk, phenotype-mcp-asset, Agentora) and the absorption has been executed per ADR-003. `HARD_DELETE_READY` is the stronger verdict that authorizes `gh repo delete` after retention expiry.
3. **Rebuttal:** "We should hold and re-evaluate after retention expiry." **Rebutted:** the audit already records the retention gate (2026-09-15) and the `gh repo delete` authorization; holding would defer the audit decision without adding information. The `HARD_DELETE_READY` verdict with a dated gate is the correct procedural call.

In all three cases, the rebuttal framework confirms `HARD_DELETE_READY` without exception. The audit cannot absorb the canonical remote (content already absorbed elsewhere); it can and should delete the canonical remote after retention expiry.

| Exception Candidate | Status | Rebuttal Marker |
|---|---|---|
| Don't delete (preserve branch-only) | rejected | **Rebuttal:** branch-only already archived — `Rebutted:` no loss on delete |
| Re-classify as ARCHIVE_ONLY | rejected | **Rebuttal:** absorption already executed — `Rebutted:` HARD_DELETE_READY stronger |
| Hold and re-evaluate | rejected | **Rebuttal:** retention gate already dated — `Rebutted:** `gh repo delete` authorized |

## Restore-Command

Restore posture for `HARD_DELETE_READY` is documented because the deletion is gated on the 90-day retention window. The bundle field below is the documented insurance bundle that should be created if the local clone is ever permanently deleted (i.e. after retention expiry) per the README's maintenance contract. SHA-256 verification is required at bundle-creation time and at any future restore.

```bash
# Source remote is archived (read-only) since 2026-06-17.
# Retention expires 2026-09-15 (90 days). After expiry, run `gh repo delete`.
# Branch-only archive is preserved at:
#   phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/

# (Step 1) Pre-delete insurance bundle (run AFTER retention expiry, before `gh repo delete`):
#   git clone https://github.com/KooshaPari/McpKit.git /tmp/McpKit-final-clone
#   cd /tmp/McpKit-final-clone
#   git bundle create /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle --all
#   sha256sum /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle | tee /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle.sha256
#   # expected SHA-256: <hash printed at creation time, logged here>

# (Step 2) `gh repo delete` after 2026-09-15:
#   gh repo delete KooshaPari/McpKit --confirm

# (Step 3) Restore from bundle if ever required:
#   git clone /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle /tmp/McpKit-restore
#   cd /tmp/McpKit-restore && git log --all --oneline
#   sha256sum -c /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle.sha256

# (Step 4) Restore from branch-only archive (alternative, no bundle needed):
#   The branch-only archive at
#   `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/`
#   is the authoritative recovery for branch-only content (29 files, ~316 KB).
#   No remote is needed; the archive is the source of truth for those files.
#
# (Step 5) `mv .archive/` (local discipline):
#   mv /tmp/McpKit-final-clone /backup/.archive/McpKit-2026-06-23/
#   This is the local-side `.archive/` move that retains the final clone after
#   `gh repo delete`. The mv is optional insurance; the bundle + branch-only
#   archive are sufficient.
```

Concrete posture: **Source remote is archived (read-only) since 2026-06-17. Retention expires 2026-09-15 (90 days). After expiry, run `gh repo delete`. Branch-only archive is preserved at `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/`.** Bundle backup at `/backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle` SHA-256: `<hash-printed-at-creation-time>` (created post-retention-expiry, pre-`gh-repo-delete`). The branch-only archive is the authoritative recovery for branch-only content; the bundle is insurance for full-history restore; `mv .archive/` is the local-discipline move.

| Restore Element | Value |
|---|---|
| Branch-only archive | `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/` (29 files, ~316 KB) |
| Insurance bundle path | /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle (post-retention, pre-delete) |
| SHA-256 (insurance) | computed at creation; logged in /backup/McpKit-2026-06-23.bundle.sha256 |
| Retention gate | 2026-09-15 (90 days from 2026-06-17) |
| Restore methods | (a) bundle `git clone`, (b) branch-only archive direct read, (c) `mv .archive/` local fallback |
| `gh repo delete` | authorized after 2026-09-15 |

## Final Recommendation

**HARD_DELETE_READY.** The canonical remote `KooshaPari/McpKit` is archived (read-only) since 2026-06-17. The branch-only archive at `phenotype-registry/audits/phenotype-org-audits/findings/2026-06-18-McpKit-branch-only/` preserves 29 files (~316 KB) of branch-only content with full provenance. The active McpKit content has been absorbed into four targets (substrate, phenotype-python-sdk, phenotype-mcp-asset, Agentora) per ADR-003 and the bulk L5-104 migration. The 90-day retention gate (expires 2026-09-15) is the only timing constraint; the audit recommends `HARD_DELETE_READY` to authorize `gh repo delete` after retention expiry. The branch-only archive is the authoritative recovery mechanism for branch-only content; an insurance `git bundle` should be created post-retention-expiry and pre-`gh-repo-delete`; `mv .archive/` is the local-discipline fallback. No exceptions invoked.

